AROUND 70 workers were evacuated after a fire at a Rolls-Royce factory.

Emergency services were called to the blaze at the building in Inchinnan, Renfrewshire at around midday.
Police said that the fire was contained to a specific area of the building and was extinguished.
Two members of staff suffered minor smoke inhalation.
There is no risk to nearby residents, police said.
 